{
    "question_stem": "The equation of a curve is given by \\(y = x(x+1)(x-3)\\).",
    "parts": [
        {
            "part_label": "a",
            "question_text": "Find the coordinates of the points where the curve intersects the \\(x\\)-axis.",
            "solution_text": "The curve intersects the \\(x\\)-axis when \\(y=0\\).  Therefore, we solve \\(x(x+1)(x-3) = 0\\). This equation is satisfied when \\(x=0\\), \\(x+1=0\\) which gives \\(x=-1\\), or \\(x-3=0\\) which gives \\(x=3\\).  Therefore the coordinates of the points of intersection are \\((0, 0)\\), \\((-1, 0)\\), and \\((3, 0)\\)."
        }
    ],
